doc.after: A fighter aircraft is a military aircraft designed primarily for air to air combat against other aircraft 1 as opposed to bombers and attack aircraft whose main mission is to attack ground targets The hallmarks of a fighter are its speed maneuverability and small size relative to other combat aircraft
